        "notes": "The stoichiometry of ternary compositions can easily be tuned by replacing the BiCl3 precursor with equivalent moles of SbCl3. The synthesis work was performed via MW-assisted thermolysis reaction inside a 100 mL Teflon vessel, in 4 parallel reaction vessels at a single run. The product (dark powder), which is about 2 g per vessel, was then cooled down to room temperature. The multivessel high pressure rotor was used for the MW synthesis work, where only four of the fifteen reactor positions were more than enough to prepare large quantity (>8 g) of the desired materials in a single run."
